data.content:
noun
plural -outs
US
[noncount] :food that is cooked in a restaurant and taken by a customer to be eaten in another place
We ordered some Chinese takeout. - called also (chiefly US) carryout, (Brit) takeaway
[count] :a restaurant that sells takeout
She works in a Chinese takeout. - called also (chiefly US) carryout, (Brit) takeaway
